{"word":"Βακχεύω","slug":"Βακχεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Βακχεύω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Βάκχος'><el>Βάκχος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to keep the feast of Bacchus, celebrate his mysteries</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to speak</i> or <i>act like one frantic</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>bacchari</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Causal, <i>to inspire with frenzy</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}